text: Ananteris sabineae is a species of scorpions. It has a pale pigmentation of its pedipalps and legs, and a dark pigmentation of its carapace. It also has less yellow spots. It is closely related to Ananteris pydanieli. == References == * Category:Buthidae Category:Animals described in 2001 Category:Arthropods of South America Category:Fauna of French Guiana Category:Scorpions of South America
title: Ananteris sabineae
